Frankly, I doubt there's a more reliable site for in-depth football statistics.

Just like to clarify a few things: both "best" and "greatest" are regarded as peacock terms (according to MOS:PEACOCK), they are broadly synonymous (particularly in the sport), so this strange distinction would appear to be in error; also Nampa DC, it was actually 2a02:c7f:fb10:1700:985f:2b01:917a:1ebd who altered the description to "best" rather than "one of the best". Xavi is at the summit, but there are others like Iniesta and Zidane, so "one of" is safer. "Best Spanish" oe is superfluous.
